  "key_observations_html": "<div style=\"border:1px solid #C7D8E8;border-radius:10px;padding:0.75rem 0.95rem;margin:0.1rem 0 0.55rem;background:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 1px 3px rgba(15,23,42,0.06);\"><ul style=\"margin:0.1rem 0 0 1.05rem;padding:0;color:#1F4C67;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.45;\"><li><strong>Stablecoin printed metrics were roughly flat this week:</strong> Market Cap near $299.07B (-0.0% 30D) means crypto dollar liquidity did not re-price hard\u2014incremental demand is coming from product and banking-rail headlines rather than a market-cap surge. Related: <a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/07/20/amazon-japan-supplier-az-com-maruwa-to-adopt-yen-stablecoin-jpyc-for-payments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Amazon Japan supplier AZ-Com Maruwa to adopt yen stablecoin JPYC for payments</a> (CoinDesk).</li><li><strong>Stablecoin market structure remains concentration-led:</strong> leadership is still defined by a small set of large issuers/platforms; share shifts matter as much as aggregate market-cap growth. Related: <a href=\"https://cointelegraph.com/news/japanese-logistics-company-eyes-jpyc-stablecoin-to-pay-drivers?utm_source=rss_feed&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=rss_partner_inbound\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Japanese logistics company eyes JPYC stablecoin to pay drivers</a> (CoinTelegraph).</li><li><strong>Bank rails are pushing stablecoins into treasury workflows:</strong> That pushes demand toward treasury and settlement use cases, not only exchange trading liquidity. Related: <a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/07/20/bank-of-korea-prepares-for-live-cbdc-transactions-with-nine-banks-in-september\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bank of Korea prepares for live CBDC transactions with 9 banks in September</a> (CoinDesk).</li></ul><p class=\"takeaways__note\">Context only\u2014not investment advice. Bullets combine on-page data with recent industry headlines.</p></div><p class=\"review-note ko-disclaimer\">Key observations are AI generated and should be reviewed for accuracy.</p>",
